    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ariadne-entry\"><p><strong>Source:</strong> Ariadne's Book of Legends - Alpha v1.2, p. 90.</p><p>Tier III: Herald</p><p>Prerequisite: Words Beyond Worlds</p><p>Immortal Echo. You are immune to the frightened and charmed conditions. If you fall unconscious or die but your body is not destroyed, your voice continues to echo, allowing you to speak and cast spells as if you were conscious until the end of your next turn. If you are dying, this effect also stabilizes you at the end of that turn.</p><p>Word of Creation. As an action, you speak a word of creation, replicating the effects of any spell of 9th level or lower that you are familiar with. Once you use this ability, you cannot do so again until you finish a long rest.</p><p>Path Connections</p><p>Sovereign. Instead of the Divine Arrival Heroic Perk, you can take the Greater Charms Perk, changing to the Sovereign path.</p><p>Overlord. Instead of the Divine Arrival Heroic Perk, you can take the Thrall Perk, changing to the Overlord path.</p></div>",
